Manhattan and Q-Q plot¶

Load gwaslab¶

In [1]:
Copied! 
import gwaslab as gl
import gwaslab as gl

Load data into Sumstats Object¶

Copied! 
mysumstats = gl.Sumstats("t2d_bbj.txt.gz",
             snpid="SNP",
             chrom="CHR",
             pos="POS",
             ea="ALT",
             nea="REF",
             neaf="Frq",
             p="P")

let's annotate 1:154309595_TA_T and 2:27734972_G_A with its nearest gene names!

anno="GENENAME" : automatically annoatate the nearest gene name

anno_set= the set of variants you want to annotate

In [13]:

4. highlight loci&pinpoint variant¶

In [15]:
Copied! 
mysumstats.plot_mqq(skip=3,cut=20,
                    anno_set=["1:154309595_TA_T","2:27734972_G_A"],
                    highlight=["19:46166604_C_T","1:154309595_TA_T"],
